- integer vector add/sub/mult/divide/compare support and 2000 torture tests
  dg-require-effective-target vect_int
- run the peephole checks directly in the codegen pass.
  it only needs to check at the beginning of each node against the previously
  last emitted line. So store at the last line of each node the pattern to
  check against, if it would be a peep pattern. See peep patterns 1-5. Then
  we can spare the extra peep pass, and the expensive check against a string.
- optimize arena_alloc: for the SIMD checks we enforce for each string a
  min-size of 16.
  we dont need that, only for the very end of a 4MB chunk. we can keep min-size 8.
- add -O2 passes, like -finline and -funroll, but no need for SSA analysis.
- for the CTFE check, set more pure attributes to known library function calls,
  which are pure in the given arguments. observe the purity of calls in CTFE
- optional QBE backend for -O2
- Missing C23 features (https://en.cppreference.com/c/compiler_support/23):
  _BitInt, decimal, interchange and extended float types, FENV_ACCESS.
